    "questions": [
        {
            "id": "bb33387048e9429fbed1c",
            "questionText": "A doctor is using a Doppler ultrasound to measure the blood flow in a patient's artery. The ultrasound probe emits a sound wave with a frequency of $!$7.5 \\text{ MHz}$!$. The speed of sound in the blood is approximately $!$1540 \\text{ m/s}$!$. The ultrasound machine detects a reflected frequency of $!$7.502 \\text{ MHz}$!$. Assuming the blood is flowing towards the probe, calculate the velocity of the blood flow in $!$\\text{m/s}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "ef26b634454c4c3f9c86d",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by calculating the frequency shift $!$\\Delta f$!$ which is the difference between the detected (reflected) frequency and the emitted frequency. Use the provided frequencies to compute this value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "2000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Hz",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "1700980398394cd7a7388",
                    "stepText": "Now, identify the correct Doppler ultrasound formula that relates the frequency shift $!$\\Delta f$!$, the blood flow velocity $!$ v$!$, the transmitted frequency $!$ f_0$!$, and the speed of sound $!$ c$!$. Please choose the correct formula from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27",
                        "5fd087bf-30b8-4f0e-9ea8-08c67db5840f",
                        "f09a3cf7-42e1-4878-b989-bb756bfc1f03",
                        "8004f091-3866-4725-923f-566d362ee31a",
                        "bbf4917b-1be4-4827-b1ae-ddfdaa7124a9"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta f = \\frac{2 v f_0}{c}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta f = \\frac{v f_0}{2 c}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta f = \\frac{c f_0}{2 v}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "18d0ad58a38f4c0e8fbe2",
                    "stepText": "Next, rearrange the chosen formula to solve for the blood flow velocity $!$ v$!$. What is the expression for $!$ v$!$ in terms of $!$\\Delta f, f_0,$!$ and $!$ c$!$? Please select the correct rearrangement from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27",
                        "5fd087bf-30b8-4f0e-9ea8-08c67db5840f",
                        "f09a3cf7-42e1-4878-b989-bb756bfc1f03",
                        "8004f091-3866-4725-923f-566d362ee31a",
                        "bbf4917b-1be4-4827-b1ae-ddfdaa7124a9"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ v = \\frac{\\Delta f \\cdot c}{2 f_0}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ v = \\frac{2 \\Delta f \\cdot c}{f_0}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ v = \\frac{\\Delta f \\cdot c}{f_0}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "3c4f051c5f8841f6a9b26",
                    "stepText": "Finally, substitute the values $!$\\Delta f = 2000 \\text{ Hz}$!$, $!$ c = 1540 \\text{ m/s}$!$, and $!$ f_0 = 7.5 \\times 10^{6} \\text{ Hz}$!$ into your expression for $!$ v$!$ and calculate the numerical value for the blood flow velocity.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.20533"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a20069a8-ca33-4e26-93ce-87c105e52c27",
