        {
            "id": "b3f1255980504ac6bea5d",
            "questionText": "An astronomer observes a distant galaxy emitting light with a known spectral line at a wavelength of $!$\\lambda = 656.3 \\text{ nm}$!$ (Hydrogen-alpha line). However, the astronomer measures the wavelength of this spectral line in the galaxy's light to be $!$\\lambda' = 690.0 \\text{ nm}$!$. Given that the speed of light is approximately $!$c = 3.0 \\times 10^8 \\text{ m/s}$!$, determine the galaxy's velocity relative to Earth. Is the galaxy moving towards or away from the Earth? Provide your answer in $!$\\text{m/s}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "87175b6d8cbb4d67ab384",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the formula to compute the redshift ($!$z$!$) for light. Redshift relates the observed wavelength ($!$\\lambda'$!$) to the emitted wavelength ($!$\\lambda$!$). Which of these formulas correctly represents redshift?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ba45dfc9-7996-4dda-bd14-1d7f21675597",
                        "21d1d259-b66f-4509-8897-4feba2f2b3e6"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$z = (\\lambda' - \\lambda)/\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$z = (\\lambda - \\lambda')/\\lambda'$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$z = \\lambda/\\lambda'$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "a4bf97d10dbb41dba63a3",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, using the formula you selected, calculate the redshift ($!$z$!$) with the given values $!$\\lambda = 656.3\\,nm$!$ and $!$\\lambda' = 690.0\\,nm$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.0513"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ba45dfc9-7996-4dda-bd14-1d7f21675597"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "74a5f9b8179d4177b3846",
                    "stepText": "Next, let's determine the correct formula to calculate the galaxy's velocity ($!$v$!$) using the redshift ($!$z$!$) you just found and the speed of light ($!$c$!$). Which of the following options correctly represents this relationship?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "5dab74ab-387d-4288-8961-5ac6d456b3e9",
                        "bbf4917b-1be4-4827-b1ae-ddfdaa7124a9"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = z \\cdot c$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = c/z$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = z/c$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fe03c8064d034868a610e",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the galaxy's velocity by applying the formula you selected with $!$c = 3.0 \\times 10^8\\,m/s$!$. Additionally, select the option that correctly indicates whether the galaxy is moving towards or away from Earth.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
